# <Project> — Refactor Playbook

**Stage D artifact, опциональный.** Positive guidance для safe refactor PRs — complements AP-6 (no silent deviation) и AP-19 (per-PR atomicity). AP-6 описывает что **нельзя** (silent scope expansion); этот playbook описывает что **можно делать правильно**.

Применяется когда AI/dev делает refactor (поведение **не меняется**, только структура / читаемость / performance / coupling).

---

## 1. Definition — что такое «refactor»

**Refactor:** изменение **внутренней структуры** кода **без изменения внешнего поведения**.

- ✅ Rename variable / function
- ✅ Extract method / inline method
- ✅ Move file / module
- ✅ Replace inheritance с composition (если behavior preserved)
- ✅ Improve naming для clarity
- ✅ Reduce duplication через extract common
- ✅ Improve type signatures (без changing runtime behavior)
- ✅ Performance optimization (если outputs identical)

**НЕ refactor (это feature / fix / breaking change):**

- ❌ Adding new functionality → `feat:`
- ❌ Fixing bug → `fix:`
- ❌ Changing API contracts → `feat:` + AP-18 expand-contract
- ❌ Changing observable behavior → `feat:` или `fix:`
- ❌ Removing functionality (without deprecation cycle) → `feat:` + AP-18

Если **поведение меняется** — это **не refactor**. Commit message `refactor:` enforce'ит discipline.

---

## 2. Pre-refactor checklist

Перед началом refactor PR:

- [ ] **Baseline tests pass** — current implementation полностью покрыта tests (или сделать coverage first as separate PR)
- [ ] **Scope clear** — что именно refactoring, why, что НЕ меняется
- [ ] **Atomic** — PR соответствует AP-19 (один domain). Если refactor cross-cuts domains — split на ordered PRs
- [ ] **No mixed concerns** — refactor PR содержит **только** refactor changes, не bundles с feature work
- [ ] **Performance baseline** (если performance refactor) — measured before, target documented

---

## 3. Refactor execution discipline

### 3.1. Tests первыми (Tests First принцип сохраняется)

**Baseline tests должны pass до начала refactor.** Если existing tests inadequate для covering refactored code:

1. PR 1: extend test coverage to baseline (`test:` commit)
2. PR 2: refactor (`refactor:` commit) — tests должны continue pass

Сначала test coverage, потом refactor. Это classic Working Effectively with Legacy Code pattern.

### 3.2. Small steps

Каждый refactor — small step:
- Extract method (one at a time)
- Rename (одна symbol per commit)
- Move file (one file per commit)

Большой refactor → много small commits в feature branch → squash при merge (если хочется one commit в main) или keep separate (если history valuable).

### 3.3. Tests pass после каждого step

После каждого small step — run tests. Если падают → step has subtle behavior change → revert + reconsider.

**Если tests падают в refactor PR — это `request-changes` finding** от reviewer'а: «refactor changed behavior; либо это feature (rename commit), либо bug fix (rename), либо нужно адресовать tests».

### 3.4. Before/after test snapshot

Documented в PR description:

```markdown
## Refactor scope
- What: <конкретное изменение>
- Why: <reason — clarity / coupling / performance / etc>
- What's NOT changing: <observable behavior list>

## Test snapshot
- Tests before: <count> passing
- Tests after: <count> passing
- New tests added (если applicable): <list>
- Coverage before: X%
- Coverage after: X% (should be ≥ before)
```

---

## 4. Common refactor patterns + safety rails

### 4.1. Rename (variable / function / module)

**Safe approach:**
1. IDE-driven rename (поддерживается VS Code / IntelliJ / etc) — refactors всё transitively + verifies references
2. Run tests
3. Commit с `refactor: rename X to Y`

**Anti-patterns:**
- Manual find-replace без verifying scope (может ломать unrelated code)
- Rename + remove deprecation alias в одном PR (breaking change; use AP-18 expand-contract если public API)

### 4.2. Extract method / extract module

**Safe approach:**
1. Identify duplication / overly-long function
2. Extract в new function/module с same behavior (identical inputs/outputs)
3. Replace original code с calls к extracted
4. Run tests
5. Commit с `refactor: extract <name>`

### 4.3. Inline method (opposite of extract)

**Safe approach:**
1. Method used в 1-2 places only + thin wrapper
2. Replace calls с inlined body
3. Remove unused method
4. Run tests

### 4.4. Move file / module

**Safe approach:**
1. Use IDE move refactor (updates imports automatically)
2. Verify imports updated across codebase
3. Run tests
4. Commit с `refactor: move X to Y`

### 4.5. Replace inheritance с composition

Complex refactor. Approach:
1. Add composition (new instance member containing previously-inherited dependency)
2. Delegate methods к composition (replace `super.method()` calls с `composed.method()`)
3. Tests should continue pass
4. Remove inheritance relationship
5. Run tests
6. Commit (или несколько коммитов per step)

**Behavioral preservation critical** — если sub-behavior changes (например, super-class behavior had side effect), может ломать.

### 4.6. Performance refactor

**Safe approach:**
1. Baseline measurement (latency / memory / throughput) — documented в PR
2. Implement optimization
3. Verify identical outputs (property-based tests preferable)
4. Re-measure — improvement documented
5. Run всё existing tests

**Anti-patterns:**
- Optimization без measurement (premature optimization)
- Optimization that changes outputs (это feature, не refactor)

---

## 5. Reviewer expectations (cross-ref AP-20)

Refactor PR triggers same review chain как любой PR:

- **protocol-compliance-reviewer** verifies:
  - Commit message `refactor:` (Conventional Commits)
  - No behavior changes documented
  - Tests continue passing (per-diff coverage не decrease)
  - Scope атомарный per AP-19

- **Domain-specific reviewer** (backend / frontend / database / etc) verifies:
  - Refactor доменно-appropriate (e.g. backend refactor проходит backend-reviewer checks)
  - No subtle behavior changes
  - Performance не deteriorated

- **design-reviewer NOT spawned** для pure refactor (нет UX semantics changes)

**Verdict expectations:**
- `approve` если everything clean
- `approve-with-comments` для minor nits (naming preference / etc)
- `request-changes` если behavior actually changed (refactor mislabeled — should be `feat:` / `fix:`)

---

## 6. Frequency / cadence

Refactor PRs — **continuous improvement**, не «спецоперация» когда tech debt overwhelms. Practice:

- **Boy Scout Rule:** when touching code для feature/fix, leave it better than found (small refactors in same PR if scope-аtomic)
- **Dedicated refactor PR** для bigger refactors (e.g. module restructure) — separate PR, focused review
- **Quarterly refactor pass** для accumulated debt (см. `tech-debt-registry.md` если applicable)

---

## 7. Tech debt — when to refactor vs accept

Не каждое imperfection заслуживает refactor PR. Decision matrix:

| Symptom | Refactor когда |
|---|---|
| Code duplication | > 3 places identical logic, и planning to extend |
| Long function | > 50 lines + planning to modify |
| God class | > 500 lines + planning to add member |
| Poor naming | When confusion blocks new work |
| Slow code | Measured performance regression |
| Tight coupling | When trying to test in isolation fails |

**Не refactor когда:**
- Code works, никто не trying to extend, no actual pain
- Refactor PR would block urgent work
- Refactor scope extends > 1 sprint without clear benefit
- It's «code I would write differently» — taste, не tech debt

---

## 8. Connect to AP-6 + AP-19

- **AP-6 (no silent deviation):** AI **никогда** не refactors silently as part of feature PR. Если AI замечает refactor opportunity during feature work — flag PM/operator, separate PR.
- **AP-19 (per-PR atomicity):** refactor PR = single scope. Не mix refactor + feature в одном PR.
- **AP-18 (deploy safety):** behavior-preserving refactors usually rollback-safe (по definition behavior same). Но если refactor включает internal API changes used by other modules — может всё равно требоваться expand-contract если эти modules are deployed separately.

